{"lemma":"مُبْهَمٌ","slug":"مُبْهَمٌ","root":"ب.ه.م","root_slug":"ب-ه-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ه-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3460"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%87%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"mysterious, secret, cloudy, uncertain"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"ambiguous, vague"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"closed, locked (a door)"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of أَبْهَمَ (ʔabhama, “to shut/lock, conceal, to make obscure”)."},"ipa":["/mub.ham/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3460","headword_ar":"مُبْهَمٌ","root":"bhm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a door,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Closed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"locked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so that one cannot find the way to open it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stopped up:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a lock upon it, with which it is fastened."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.) ―         -b2-  A wall"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in which is no door."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  A chest"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no lock"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of which it may be opened"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (IAmb, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muSomatN","text_ar":"مُصْمَتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Solid; not hollow;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSomatu","text_ar":"اَصْمَتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which signifies the same]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abohamu","text_ar":"اَبْهَمُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no fissure in it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓ the latter, applied to a heart is said to mean (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impenetrable by admonition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  A thing, or an affair,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made to be dubious, confused,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vague;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such that there is no way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of knowing it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see the verb;)] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such that one knows not the way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, in which it should be engaged in, done, executed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"performed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, S, Mgh, TA:) (assumed tropical:)  speech, or language, ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is dubious, confused,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vague,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such that there is no way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of knowing it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA:) applied to a road, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unapparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hardly apparent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and, applied to the ordinance respecting the making up for the days in which one has broken a fast, [and to many other cases,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"undefined;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this instance meaning, as to whether the days may be interrupted, or whether they must be consecutive. (Mgh.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubohamaAtN","text_ar":"مُبْهَمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Difficult things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affairs, such that one cannot find the way to perform them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^asomaA='u Almubohamapu","text_ar":"الاَسْمَا=ءُ المُبْهَمَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", so termed by the grammarians, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The nouns of indication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`w^ulaA='i","text_ar":"هٰوُلَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*aAka","text_ar":"ذَاكَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uwlaAy^ika","text_ar":"اُولَايِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) accord. to Az,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHuruwfu Almubohamapu","text_ar":"الحُرُوفُ المُبْهَمَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the particles which have no derivatives, and of which the roots are not known, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al~a*iY","text_ar":"الَّذِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano","text_ar":"مَنْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  Applied to a vow, and to [certain ordinances respecting] marriage and divorce and emancipation, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"From which there is no getting out,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extricating of oneself; as though they were closed doors with locks upon them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) and, applied to prohibited things, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not allowable in any manner,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nor for any cause;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prohibited unconditionally;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as the prohibition of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the marriage with"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the mother, and the sister,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Mgh, * K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, TA:) such a woman is said to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubohamapN EalaY Alr~ajuli","text_ar":"مُبْهَمَةٌ عَلَى الرَّجُلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"absolutely prohibited to the man; as though she were closed against him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inaccessible to him"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb. [But in this last work it seems to be"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mvbohimapN","text_ar":"مثبْهِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is not agreeable with common usage.]) In the copies of the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buhomN","text_ar":"بُهْمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buhumN","text_ar":"بُهُمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are given as pls. of this word: but it seems that there is an omission or a misplacement in the passage; for these are said to be pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahiymN","text_ar":"بَهِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as shown above. (TA.) ―         -b7-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In a state of swooning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"insensibility, speechless, and without discrimination;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in consequence of a blow [&c.]. (TA.) ―         -b8-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahiymN","text_ar":"بَهِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["JK","K","TA","S","Mgh","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}